This paper is about language modelling using recurrent neural networks, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the computer science category of "Computation and Language" (cs.CL). The paper also discusses optimization techniques for improving the efficiency of the model, which could fall under "Machine Learning" (cs.LG) and "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI). The use of neural networks also suggests the possibility of it being categorized under "Neural and Evolutionary Computing" (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses memory optimization, which could fall under "Systems and Control" (cs.SY).
